    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 is a concours-level example of the E46 chassis, powered by the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six featuring individual throttle bodies and a 7,900 RPM redline. Mechanically flawless, this unit has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance including a dual-VANOS overhaul, rod bearing replacement with ARP bolts, and a structural subframe reinforcement. The Getrag 6-speed manual transmission shifts with clinical precision, delivering power to the rear wheels through a factory limited-slip differential. The suspension is optimized with Bilstein PSS10 dampers, providing exceptional damping control without compromising the car's balanced kinematics. The exterior retains its factory depth and clarity, free of rock chips or typical trim oxidation. This is a turn-key, investment-grade specimen for the serious collector.",
